---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Navbar from '../components/Navbar.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy — Checkout Ninja"
  description="Privacy Policy for Checkout Ninja by Nex App Studio. Learn how we handle your data securely."
>
  <Navbar />
  <main class="pt-16">
    <!-- Header -->
    <section class="py-16 lg:py-24">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 text-center">
        <h1 class="font-heading font-bold text-4xl sm:text-5xl lg:text-6xl text-gray-900 mb-4">
          Privacy Policy
        </h1>
        <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm">Last updated: March 7, 2026</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Content -->
    <section class="pb-16 lg:pb-24">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 prose prose-gray prose-headings:font-heading prose-headings:font-semibold prose-a:text-mint-500 hover:prose-a:text-mint-600">
        <p>
          This Privacy Policy describes how Nex App Studio ("we", "us", "our") collects, uses, and protects information when you use the Checkout Ninja app ("the App").
        </p>

        <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>We access only the data Shopify provides through the Checkout Extensibility framework.</li>
          <li>We do not independently collect, store, or process customer personal data outside of what Shopify provides.</li>
          <li>Merchant account information (name, email, store URL) is collected when you install the app through Shopify.</li>
          <li>App configuration and settings data (block configurations, rules, templates) is stored to provide the service.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>2. How We Use Information</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>To provide and maintain the Checkout Ninja app.</li>
          <li>To process your block configurations, rules, and templates.</li>
          <li>To provide customer support.</li>
          <li>To send important updates about the app (feature changes, service notices).</li>
          <li>We do not sell, rent, or share your data with third parties for marketing purposes.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>3. Data Storage & Security</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>All data is processed through Shopify's secure infrastructure.</li>
          <li>We follow industry-standard security practices to protect your information.</li>
          <li>App configuration data is stored securely and is only accessible to your store.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>4. Third-Party Services</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>The app may integrate with third-party services when merchants enable features like API validation, address validation, or gift card validation.</li>
          <li>These integrations are configured by the merchant and data is sent to the merchant's own specified endpoints.</li>
          <li>We are not responsible for the privacy practices of third-party services configured by the merchant.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>5. Cookies & Tracking</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>The Checkout Ninja website may use cookies for analytics (Google Analytics) and essential site functionality.</li>
          <li>You can control cookie preferences through your browser settings.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>6. Your Rights</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>You can request access to your data at any time.</li>
          <li>You can request deletion of your data by uninstalling the app or contacting us.</li>
          <li>You can request a copy of any data we hold about your store.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>7. Data Retention</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>We retain your data for as long as you have the app installed.</li>
          <li>Upon uninstallation, configuration data is deleted within 30 days.</li>
          <li>We may retain minimal records as required by law.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>8. Children's Privacy</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Checkout Ninja is a B2B service for Shopify Plus merchants.</li>
          <li>We do not knowingly collect information from children under 16.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>9. Changes to This Policy</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time.</li>
          <li>We will notify merchants of significant changes via email or in-app notification.</li>
          <li>Continued use of the app after changes constitutes acceptance.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>10. Contact Us</h2>
        <p>
          For privacy-related questions, contact us at: <a href="mailto:support@nexappstudio.com">support@nexappstudio.com</a>
        </p>
        <p>Nex App Studio, Sharjah, UAE</p>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>
